ParagonWiki.Wiki.TutorialDef.text:
Steam energy is the first phase of energy development in our modpack.

Steam structures follow a modular principle. So, to produce steam, a steam generator must be connected to boilers that produce heat, as well as to barrels of water.
The type of fuel for boilers affects the efficiency of the generator.
{Image(path="Core/Tutorials/SteamPower/1", size="(510, 418)")}

The resulting steam can be used in steam engines or engines to produce electricity.
{Image(path="Core/Tutorials/SteamPower/2", size="(510, 186)")}

They must be attached close to the steam generator, according to the diagram.
{Image(path="Core/Tutorials/SteamPower/3", size="(510, 389)")}

There are several stages in the development of steam generators, which make it possible to support the simultaneous operation of several machines at once.

